[Patient] How often should I exercise to manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week. Start small and gradually increase. 
[Patient] I don't have money for a gym membership. What are my options?
[Educator] You can try bodyweight exercises at home, like squats, lunges, and push-ups. 
[Patient] I struggle to find motivation to exercise. Any tips?
[Educator] Set achievable goals, find a workout buddy for support, and reward yourself for progress. 
[Patient] Is it safe for me to exercise with my heart failure condition?
[Educator] Start slowly and listen to your body. Stop if you feel dizzy, short of breath, or have chest pain. 
[Patient] What are the benefits of exercise for managing heart failure?
[Educator] Exercise can improve heart health, reduce symptoms, and enhance your quality of life. 
[Patient] How can I fit exercise into my busy schedule?
[Educator] Try to schedule short workout sessions throughout the day. Even 10 minutes at a time can help. 
